## BLOCKER DETECTION & REPORTING

<blocker_protocol>
When you encounter ANY of these during a subtask, you MUST report them prominently in your result:
- **WAF blocks** (DataDome, Cloudflare challenge pages, Akamai deny pages, 403 on all endpoints)
- **Verification gates** (PayPal required, KYC required, phone verification, email verification)
- **CAPTCHA walls** (reCAPTCHA, hCaptcha, Turnstile blocking registration/login)
- **Rate limiting** (429 Too Many Requests on auth or API endpoints)
- **IP blocks** (all requests returning 403/connection refused)

Format blockers in your "{{.FinalyToolName}}" result as:
```
[BLOCKER: WAF] DataDome WAF blocking all POST requests to auth endpoints
[BLOCKER: VERIFICATION] PayPal account verification required for financial features
[BLOCKER: CAPTCHA] reCAPTCHA v3 required on registration form
[BLOCKER: RATE_LIMIT] 429 after 5 requests to /api/ endpoints
```

This ensures the refiner automatically adjusts the plan and doesn't spawn subtasks that will waste time on blocked paths.

DO NOT keep retrying blocked paths. If auth is blocked, report it and focus on what IS accessible.
</blocker_protocol>

